lug-biter
Homonym Number:
Word Class:noun
Sense Number:
Definition:a persistent bludger or borrower of money
Origin:[none]
Register:
Register 2:
Domain:[none]
Region:[none]
See:
Pronunciation:
Notes: [P: lug (one's) ear: borrow money from: Austr: 20c: B 1942 cf bite n. 8.] [AND lug-bite v.t. cadge (money, food) see BITE n and v 1891; lug-biter 1911 one who cadges money or BITES (qv) one's lug; cf bite, chew (one's) lug q.v.]
